		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.68]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Slipskin&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>The big reason for doing 2HB, IMO, is not the damage per hit.&nbsp;&nbsp;A pair of good one handers will ultimately do as good if not better damage output over time.  The big reason for 2HB (with a few rare and expensive exceptions) is damage shields. Not yours. The mobs.  Fast 1 handers will cause you to do a lot of damage to yourself.  Many a rogue, monk and beastlord has beat themselves to death on mob damage shields.  2HB's have a much slower hit speed.  That means fewer hits over time. So less damage from damage shields.  Yes, a 2 hander will do more damage on any single hit.  That is why they are still feasible as weapons.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
