		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=235332"><span id=Scholar>Auricas</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>57 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.98]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Auricas&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>For raising 2hb weapon skill, I would not necessarily look at the place you plan on doing, but the weapon you plan on training with. <br><br>If I'm not mistaken (and somebody correct me if I'm wrong), you can only get better at a weapon skill, like 2hb, if you actually land hits.&nbsp;&nbsp;Missing will not yield skill-ups.  So with this in mind, it's a good idea to get a 2hb weapon with a low delay, as low as possible.  With such a weapon, you will swing more in any given amount of time, and so land more hits, and therefore get more skill-ups.  I used a Bamboo Bo Stick (I think that's the name) that has something like 20 delay and 8 damage.  They are pretty cheap, around 400p on The Rathe server.  It did almost nothing in damage, but my skill was raised a lot faster than when I used other, slower 2hb's.  Then once you have maxed your skill, switch to another 2hb with a better delay/damage ratio for normal damage output.  <br><br>So where ever you might go to grind experience, and you want to practice the 2hb, just let the group know that you will be doing it.  A lot of groups, especially at lower levels, won't mind.  Even just doing it for a few monsters each time you group will raise it well enough, without sacrificing all that much in damage over the duration of your group.<br><br>PS:  Wu's Quivering Staff would be a perfect weapon for raising that 2hb skill, BUT it has a weight of 10.  10!!!  I've always thought this was backwards and mistake on the developer's part.  A monk weapon that has such a weight, when monks get penalties for having too much of it.  I suppose if you don't plan on getting hit, it would do just fine.  </p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Auricas<br>65 Monk<br>The Rathe<br></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
